solutions.content:
You recursively add/sub one ***unit*** at a time.

Without the dp-matrix, the solution is 2 ms.
With it, the code runs at a ***healthy*** 2,490 ms.
```
class Solution {

    int[][] dp;

    public int sum(int num1, int num2) {
        dp = new int[202][202];
        for(int i = 0; i < dp.length; i++)
            Arrays.fill(dp[i], Integer.MAX_VALUE);

        return helper(num1, num2);
    }

    private int helper(int num1, int num2) {
        if(num1 == 0 && num2 == 0)
            return 0;

        if(dp[num1 + 100][num2 + 100] != Integer.MAX_VALUE)
            return dp[num1][num2];

        int answer;
        if(num1 < 0)
            answer = -1 + sum(num1 + 1, num2);
        else if(num2 < 0)
            answer = -1 + sum(num1, num2 + 1);
        else if(num1 > 0)
            answer = 1 + sum(num1 - 1, num2);
        else //if(num2 > 0)
            answer = 1 + sum(num1, num2 - 1);

        dp[num1 + 100][num2 + 100] = answer;

        return answer;
    }
}
```

