# Intuition
After long nights of thinking about the algorithems that needed to be implemented to actually get the right answers, I realized that there is actually ```unsigned int -1``` approaches to this problem. Driving me to the brink of insanity.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$O(((2-abs(log(Log_2 (12*N/2 -3)+ M^2)*4))M/2)$

- Space complexity:
`Don't Even get me started`

# Contraversial Solution
```
class Solution {
public:
    int sum(int num1, int num2) {
        return num1 + num2;
    }
};
```
# Obvious Solution
```
class Solution {
public:
    int sum(int num1, int num2) {
        std::string num1_string {to_string(num1)};
        std::string num2_string {to_string(num2)};
        auto iter1 {num1_string.begin()};
        auto iter2 {num2_string.begin()};
        std::string num1_string_compiled {};
        std::string num2_string_compiled {};
        for(int i {}; i<num1_string.size();i++){
            num1_string_compiled += *iter1;
            iter1 ++;
        }
        for(int i {}; i<num2_string.size();i++){
            num2_string_compiled += *iter2;
            iter2 ++;
        }
        return stoi(num1_string_compiled) + stoi(num2_string_compiled);

    }
};
```
