➡ https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adder_%28electronics%29#Half_adder

⏱ Since number of bits in an int is `log(x) + 1` the time compleity is `O(log(num2)`

👍🏾

```
/**
 * @param {number} num1
 * @param {number} num2
 * @return {number}
 */
var sum = function(num1, num2) {
    while (num2) {
        // carry now contains common set bits of num1 and num2
        let carry = num1 & num2;
        // Sum of bits of num1 and num2 where at least one of the bits is not set
        num1 = num1 ^ num2;
        // Carry is shifted by one so that adding it to num1 gives the required sum
        num2 = carry << 1;
    }
    return num1;
};

