# Intuition
I forgot what sum meant so I looked it up.

# Approach
At first I just tried using one for loop, but then I realized we must also be able to add negative numbers. Thus I added an if statment.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Beats 100%
O(1)

- Space complexity:
Beats 59.9%
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int sum(int num1, int num2) {
        int newint = num1;
        int newint2 = num2;

        if(newint2 > 0)
        {
            for(int i = 1; i <= newint2; i++)
            {
            newint++;
            }
        }
        else
        {
            for(int i = 1; i <= abs(newint2); i++)
            {
            newint--;
            }
        }

        return newint;
    }
};
```

