# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Just adding two numbers is too easy!

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If you do not use addition operators, then only bitwise operations remain

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(1)$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    func sum(_ num1: Int, _ num2: Int) -> Int {
// Since we use bitwise operators, we first find the 
// logical exclusive OR and get a number in which there are only "mismatched" bits
        let differentOneBits = num1 ^ num2
// Next, we find a logical AND or value, 
// containing only "matching" one-bits.
        let commonOneBits = num1 & num2
// We check if the logical And is empty, then we have come across numbers /
// that do not have "matching" bits-units, and in this case the sum will
// be the previously calculated logical exclusive OR
        guard commonOneBits != 0 else { return differentOneBits }
// If the totaled numbers have common one-bits, then at some point we sum
// up 1 + 1 bits and we need to shift the bits to the left, after which we 
// recursively call the initial method. In fact, we are doubling the value 
// of the original logical AND and looking for a combination in which 
// there will be no "matching" bits.
        return sum(differentOneBits, commonOneBits << 1)
    }
}
```

